        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Stapletons Crossroads,
or 7 miles northwest of Louisville, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Davisboro, Edge Hill, Edgehill, Downs, Agricola, Grange, and
Stapletons Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
